<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-01-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="90" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 18643/13.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Dudley</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-01-22"><hi rend="italic">January 22,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Knox directs Ambassador Dudley to express the high appreciation of
                            the Government of the United States of the action of the Brazilian
                            Congress in extending and continuing the list of American products to
                            enjoy preferential tariff treatment.</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>